The Louvre Abu Dhabi residences project is still progressively ongoing. The ultra-luxury development is located within the Saadiyat Grove community. The Louvre Abu Dhabi residences project is a collaboration between the largest UAE developer, Aldar Properties, and Louvre Abu Dhabi. The project offers a diverse range of exquisite units. The project was officially launched in the first quarter of 2022. The ultra-luxury residential development offers exquisite units. These units range from studios to 1, 2, and 3-bedroom apartments. The homes feature floor-to-ceiling windows that overlook the iconic Louvre Abu Dhabi. Read ALsoÂ Louvres Hotel Group to run the Royal Tulip Plaza Addis Ababa Hotel Additionally, the homes will be available in two distinct color schemes. The first will be Dark Premium with a rich palette of cool neutrals. These will include charcoal with slate gray undertones. The second color scheme will be Light Premium. These will feature creamy and taupe accents. The interiors will include metallic accents and marble finishes. The Louvre Abu Dhabi residences project aims to redefine the combination of life and art. Thus, every unit will include exclusive artwork within the dining and living room spaces. The project also boasts a sustainable design. The design further, adheres to the requirements of the Pearl Building Rating System. Residents will also have access to glass elevators. These will enable them to enjoy the gorgeous panoramic view while headed to their homes. It is set in a prestigious location in Abu Dhabi, Saadiyat Island. The location is surrounded by art fairs as well as amazing architecture. Further enhancing the overall experience of residents. The project is expected to begin handover by 2025.